00:00:01.469 --> 00:00:06.542
It is my immense joy

00:00:06.743 --> 00:00:15.920
to see all of you here from various parts of this world.

00:00:20.287 --> 00:00:23.097
When your heart is so full,

00:00:23.298 --> 00:00:29.454
the words are too poor to carry the intensity.

00:00:30.413 --> 00:00:41.511
I wish you could understand that intensity, through your heart.

00:00:43.633 --> 00:00:48.200
It’s all been arranged, I think, by the Divine,

00:00:48.400 --> 00:00:51.626
that we should meet here all of us

00:00:51.827 --> 00:00:57.228
in such a wonderful surrounding, in the Nature.

00:00:57.429 --> 00:01:01.179
That something great should happen to all of us.

00:01:01.380 --> 00:01:10.059
That we should achieve really something great this time.

00:01:11.940 --> 00:01:19.743
Now as the time is short, I will tell you, first of all,

00:01:19.944 --> 00:01:25.969
a few things about meditation now,

00:01:26.169 --> 00:01:31.949
then we’ll have two more talks, I hope so.

00:01:40.020 --> 00:01:47.358
‘Meditation’ is a very general word. It is not a word that explains

00:01:47.559 --> 00:01:53.519
all the three steps one has to take for meditating.

00:01:53.727 --> 00:02:01.858
But in Sanskrit language, they have very clearly said

00:02:02.058 --> 00:02:07.971
how you have to move in your meditation.

00:02:09.305 --> 00:02:14.639
First is called as dhyana,

00:02:14.840 --> 00:02:18.702
and second is called as dharana,

00:02:18.903 --> 00:02:23.359
and the third is called as samadhi.

00:02:23.560 --> 00:02:30.009
Luckily Sahaja Yoga is a, such a thing that you get everything in a bundle.

00:02:30.210 --> 00:02:34.159
You avoided everything else and you got the samadhi part.

00:02:34.360 --> 00:02:41.085
That’s the beauty of it. Firstly the dhyana.

00:02:43.717 --> 00:02:49.921
First, when you have seeking,

00:02:50.121 --> 00:03:02.460
you put your attention towards the object of your worship.

00:03:02.902 --> 00:03:07.372
That’s called as ‘dhyana’.

00:03:07.573 --> 00:03:14.816
And the dharana is the one in which you

00:03:15.017 --> 00:03:20.879
put all your effort, concentrate all your effort.

00:03:21.080 --> 00:03:26.381
But this is all drama for people who are not Realised.

00:03:26.903 --> 00:03:34.630
For them it’s just a sort of an acting that they do,

00:03:34.831 --> 00:03:42.879
but for a Realised-soul it is a reality.

00:03:43.460 --> 00:03:50.677
So the first, the dhyana, you have to do.

00:03:55.460 --> 00:04:00.980
Some do it of the Form, another of the Formless.

00:04:01.180 --> 00:04:08.988
But you are so fortunate that the Formless has become a Form for you.

00:04:10.500 --> 00:04:13.406
No problem. You don’t have to go from form to formless

00:04:13.607 --> 00:04:20.273
and from formless to form, it’s all there, in a bundle!

00:04:21.570 --> 00:04:36.649
So you concentrate or think of some deity

00:04:36.850 --> 00:04:44.489
or some point for nirakar, for the Formless or of nirakar itself.

00:04:44.690 --> 00:04:48.739
It’s also mental projection as long as you are not a Realised-soul.

00:04:48.940 --> 00:04:58.182
But once you are Realised,
you have to just think of dhyana:

00:04:58.382 --> 00:05:06.170
[on] whom you are going

00:05:06.370 --> 00:05:10.810
to concentrate or you can say, meditate on.

00:05:11.010 --> 00:05:16.729
But once you start meditating on a person, your attention starts moving.

00:05:16.930 --> 00:05:20.619
That is also possible after Realisation.

00:05:20.820 --> 00:05:23.787
Though it’s in a bundle, but some people have it, part of it,

00:05:23.987 --> 00:05:30.460
part of it, like that. So when you meditate,

00:05:30.660 --> 00:05:38.940
still your attention can get disturbed every moment.

00:05:39.140 --> 00:05:44.540
It can happen, depending on the intensity of your concentration.

00:05:44.740 --> 00:05:47.499
So there are some Sahaja Yogis, I have seen,

00:05:47.700 --> 00:05:54.539
they are cooking, and there’s another one who is meditating.

00:05:54.740 --> 00:06:01.528
The meditating one will say, "Oh I can smell it is burning."

00:06:06.447 --> 00:06:10.459
So there is no dharana.

00:06:10.660 --> 00:06:13.419
‘Dhaar’ means a flow, a continuous flow.

00:06:13.620 --> 00:06:18.299
So there is no dharana. Dhyana is there, but not dharana.

00:06:18.500 --> 00:06:22.151
The second part of it is very important,

00:06:22.351 --> 00:06:33.019
that you have to put your attention continuously onto your deity.

00:06:33.220 --> 00:06:36.213
Then you develop a state, which is called as ‘dharana’,

00:06:36.413 --> 00:06:47.419
in which your attention becomes one with the deity.

00:06:47.620 --> 00:06:52.539
But when these mature, the third stage of samadhi comes in.

00:06:52.740 --> 00:06:58.957
Now for people who think that, without Realisation, they can do it,

00:06:59.158 --> 00:07:04.859
I think they are absolutely mistaken.

00:07:05.060 --> 00:07:15.576
But after Realisation also, when the dharana is established,

00:07:15.776 --> 00:07:23.660
you have to get to the position where you become samadhi.

00:07:23.860 --> 00:07:28.258
Now, what is that state?

00:07:28.458 --> 00:07:37.046
When that state comes into your mind, then whatever you do,

00:07:37.246 --> 00:07:43.362
the deity that you worship,

00:07:43.562 --> 00:07:48.991
you see that deity in your work.

00:07:49.192 --> 00:07:56.318
Whatever you see, you see the deity giving you the show.

00:07:56.519 --> 00:07:58.700
You can put it like that.

00:07:58.901 --> 00:08:09.180
Whatever you hear, you find the deity telling you the Truth.

00:08:09.380 --> 00:08:17.020
Whatever you read, you find there what the deity would tell you.

00:08:17.220 --> 00:08:22.945
So in that state, whatever you do

00:08:23.145 --> 00:08:30.540
with your eyes, nose and all these organs,

00:08:30.741 --> 00:08:37.802
all that becomes a kind of a manifestation

00:08:38.002 --> 00:08:43.623
of the deity whom you worship, automatically.

00:08:43.824 --> 00:08:47.099
You don’t have to think, "Now I must concentrate, alright.

00:08:47.300 --> 00:08:52.539
I will not have these thoughts, I have to now think about this."

00:08:52.740 --> 00:08:54.932
It becomes automatically that.

00:08:55.133 --> 00:08:58.347
You read a book, in that book immediately you find

00:08:58.547 --> 00:09:01.340
what is good for Sahaja Yoga.

00:09:01.540 --> 00:09:07.153
If there’s a book, which is anti-God, you discard it.

00:09:07.353 --> 00:09:09.579
Just call Marina there.

00:09:09.780 --> 00:09:22.101
But if you have a problem,

00:09:22.301 --> 00:09:32.380
you see that, "It must be for some lesson to me.

00:09:32.580 --> 00:09:37.740
That it is to teach me some experience."

00:09:37.940 --> 00:09:42.220
It is the manifestation of the deity itself.

00:09:42.420 --> 00:09:45.819
For example a lady feels she is going to have an abortion,

00:09:46.019 --> 00:09:49.593
take a position.

00:09:49.793 --> 00:09:54.940
So one person who is not yet in samadhi avasta,

00:09:55.140 --> 00:09:58.965
or condition, will say, "Oh God, I am such a Sahaja Yogi,

00:09:59.165 --> 00:10:04.505
I have done so much for Mother. I went all the way to Pulborough thing,

00:10:04.705 --> 00:10:09.603
and, despite that, see, this is the problem!"

00:10:10.980 --> 00:10:15.820
But another would say that, "Alright let me try. I’ll go and tell Mother."

00:10:16.020 --> 00:10:19.739
On the photograph, or maybe telephone, something.

00:10:19.940 --> 00:10:24.940
And he’ll find, to his surprise, that it’s all done.

00:10:25.140 --> 00:10:28.780
It’s perfectly alright.

00:10:28.980 --> 00:10:32.780
This is only possible if you are a Realised-soul, otherwise not possible.

00:10:32.980 --> 00:10:37.475
So the state that is awakened within you is called,

00:10:37.675 --> 00:10:41.278
is a new state of mind, in Sanskrit language

00:10:41.478 --> 00:10:44.676
it has a very beautiful name is ‘Rutumbhara Pradnya’.

00:10:44.877 --> 00:10:49.029
Which is a very difficult name. Rutumbhara Pradnya.

00:10:49.230 --> 00:10:53.820
Rutumbhara means the whole, Rutumbhara is the name of the Nature.

00:10:54.020 --> 00:11:02.975
And that the whole Nature, one feels, is enlightened.

00:11:04.340 --> 00:11:08.877
I’ll give an example: when a child is to be born,

00:11:09.077 --> 00:11:15.730
the mother starts lactating, automatically.

00:11:16.500 --> 00:11:22.620
The Nature itself works out for the birth of the child.

00:11:22.820 --> 00:11:27.041
In the same way, when this Rutumbhara Pradnya,

00:11:27.241 --> 00:11:33.803
starts expressing itself - only for Sahaja Yogis, nobody else -

00:11:34.003 --> 00:11:36.500
you are amazed how things work out suddenly.

00:11:36.701 --> 00:11:39.362
Rutumbhara Pradnya it works out.

00:11:39.563 --> 00:11:45.260
Now the time is very short, but I’ll give you an example.

00:11:45.460 --> 00:11:50.434
I came to Brighton,

00:11:50.634 --> 00:11:53.260
and Jason said, "Mother let’s have Guru Puja in Brighton".

00:11:53.460 --> 00:11:58.940
I said, "Alright, have it, but you find out the place."

00:11:59.140 --> 00:12:02.140
So he went to the university, said, "The university people will help,

00:12:02.340 --> 00:12:05.660
but it’s rather small and…" I said, "But ask them".

00:12:05.860 --> 00:12:07.985
"But no, it’s booked on Guru Puja." Then I said,

00:12:08.186 --> 00:12:10.780
"Then what can you do?" He said, "Then what to do Mother?"

00:12:10.980 --> 00:12:15.179
I said, "You try somewhere else just now, telephone to somebody else."

00:12:15.380 --> 00:12:17.873
So he went through yellow pages, I don’t know what, and he telephoned,

00:12:18.074 --> 00:12:21.687
and they said, "We have a place, a beautiful place,

00:12:21.887 --> 00:12:27.751
and you come along and have lunch with us."

00:12:27.952 --> 00:12:30.619
And just he went there, he had a very nice lunch,

00:12:30.819 --> 00:12:33.739
they were very happy [that] they were to accommodate everyone.

00:12:33.940 --> 00:12:36.468
They were very nice, and he was amazed

00:12:36.668 --> 00:12:40.229
how everything has worked out so well.

00:12:40.429 --> 00:12:47.600
So the Rutumbhara Pradnya has started working in your favour.

00:12:47.800 --> 00:12:50.537
You all tell me, "This is a miracle, that has happened Mother,

00:12:50.738 --> 00:12:54.244
and we don’t know how it has happened!" I’ll give you an example:

00:12:54.444 --> 00:12:57.266
Yesterday, you we were doing something with cement

00:12:57.466 --> 00:13:01.519
and the Italian boy said that we’ll need two bags of cement.

00:13:01.720 --> 00:13:05.720
I said, "You carry on, it won’t finish!" Even before I was leaving,

00:13:05.921 --> 00:13:09.122
they were carrying on, still not finished!

00:13:09.322 --> 00:13:14.592
Now cement of all the things. Imagine!

00:13:16.237 --> 00:13:20.433
So this special thing is your own state,

00:13:20.633 --> 00:13:24.704
where you are feeling the oneness with the Nature

00:13:24.904 --> 00:13:27.771
and the Nature is feeling oneness with you.

00:13:27.979 --> 00:13:31.420
So the Divine itself is expressing through Nature,

00:13:31.620 --> 00:13:39.022
through various happenings, through various incidents –

00:13:39.222 --> 00:13:47.679
the Love, the protection, the attention that the Divine is giving.

00:13:47.880 --> 00:13:50.910
And there’s no end to it.

00:13:51.111 --> 00:13:58.960
It just happens, and people don’t know how it happens.

00:13:59.160 --> 00:14:02.320
But that is what is the state of samadhi.

00:14:02.520 --> 00:14:07.360
But there could be people if I tell them,

00:14:07.560 --> 00:14:11.360
"Will you do this?" "Oh no Mother! The shop will be closed."

00:14:11.560 --> 00:14:15.053
"Oh, They won’t do it!" "That’s not alright".

00:14:15.254 --> 00:14:18.713
They go on like that. And there are people

00:14:18.913 --> 00:14:22.480
who say, "No! Let’s see. If Mother has said – maybe."

00:14:22.680 --> 00:14:26.238
I’ll give you another simple example, very simple, absolutely gross,

00:14:26.439 --> 00:14:31.920
but it’s there: One day Mr. Shrivastava, he takes one type of tea.

00:14:32.120 --> 00:14:36.347
Very English.

00:14:36.547 --> 00:14:41.049
And he wouldn’t like other tea. So he told me, "Oh God,

00:14:41.249 --> 00:14:44.159
we are finished with the tea and what to do tomorrow morning?"

00:14:44.360 --> 00:14:46.801
I said, "It’s alright, let us go to the tea shop."

00:14:47.002 --> 00:14:52.160
So he said, "It is eight o’clock in the night and what do you mean?

00:14:52.360 --> 00:14:56.479
They’ll all laugh at us! There is no shop at eight o’clock open."

00:14:56.680 --> 00:14:58.640
That tea centre. I said, "Let’s go! What’s the harm.

00:14:58.840 --> 00:15:00.799
I am just saying ‘let’s go!’ " But he said,

00:15:01.000 --> 00:15:03.680
"What absurd things you are saying!" I said, "Alright, absurd whatever it is.

00:15:03.880 --> 00:15:05.538
Let’s go!"

00:15:05.738 --> 00:15:09.131
So he wouldn’t listen so I told the driver "Alright, let’s drive down!"

00:15:09.331 --> 00:15:11.840
We went there. And the lights were on.

00:15:12.040 --> 00:15:15.839
We said, "Eh! How is it the lights are on?" (laughter)

00:15:16.040 --> 00:15:19.435
So we walked in, you see, very peevishly.

00:15:19.635 --> 00:15:22.640
And they all were there standing, "Oh we’ve been waiting for you

00:15:22.840 --> 00:15:25.825
such a long time, you know, and you are the last to come!"

00:15:26.026 --> 00:15:28.639
Just imagine! So I asked my husband.

00:15:28.840 --> 00:15:33.867
He said, "I forgot we had a reception here!" (laughter).

00:15:37.480 --> 00:15:40.880
And they said, "You are the last to arrive!"

00:15:41.081 --> 00:15:43.747
And they said, "Alright, doesn’t matter but you’ll have your presents!"

00:15:43.947 --> 00:15:49.621
So they gave us two tins each of tea! (laughter)

00:15:56.680 --> 00:16:00.079
I mean, there are thousand and one examples like that.

00:16:00.280 --> 00:16:02.719
Today like some were trying to push the bed.

00:16:02.920 --> 00:16:05.520
The three of them were trying, it would not push.

00:16:05.720 --> 00:16:09.280
I said, "Alright, I’ll push it." I just put my Nabhi there.

00:16:09.480 --> 00:16:15.276
Just, I didn’t push anything, it just pushed.

00:16:17.560 --> 00:16:20.442
Because of the Rutumbhara Pradnya .

00:16:20.643 --> 00:16:23.051
But this is not chamatkar (miracle) or anything.

00:16:23.252 --> 00:16:29.087
It exists in the Divine the capacity to manifest it’s love,

00:16:29.287 --> 00:16:36.180
to show that you are the saints, you are the chosen ones of God.

00:16:36.381 --> 00:16:39.232
But you accept that situation first. But if you behave

00:16:39.433 --> 00:16:42.620
like all other normal people, "Oh God, the shops are closed,

00:16:42.821 --> 00:16:46.586
and that man is so difficult, and I don’t think it will happen",

00:16:46.786 --> 00:16:49.599
never happen.

00:16:49.800 --> 00:16:53.055
But you must know you are saints,

00:16:53.255 --> 00:17:02.529
chosen, and given birth by me, the Form and the Formless.

00:17:02.730 --> 00:17:07.360
So this Pradnya is going to manifest, is manifesting every moment,

00:17:07.560 --> 00:17:11.130
be prepared, be happy, welcome it,

00:17:11.331 --> 00:17:17.867
and accept that you are that.
The level is different.

00:17:18.067 --> 00:17:21.820
Was done? Alright?

00:17:22.873 --> 00:17:26.433
Five minutes more.

00:17:28.019 --> 00:17:33.159
I should blame anything that side.

00:17:33.820 --> 00:17:37.239
Alright.

00:17:37.947 --> 00:17:46.040
Now the time has come for Sahaja Yoga to change it’s level.

00:17:50.200 --> 00:17:56.341
We have to change, we have to go higher, the level has to come up.

00:17:56.542 --> 00:18:00.516
But Sahaja Yoga is such a cosmopolitan thing

00:18:00.716 --> 00:18:08.118
that we have got the worst bhoots
to the highest, on the same plate.

00:18:08.824 --> 00:18:12.559
Now, some of them are round ones,

00:18:12.759 --> 00:18:19.599
which are the ego-oriented ones, who roll all the time.

00:18:19.800 --> 00:18:25.360
They don’t know how to raise the plate.
If you raise the plate they’ll roll down.

00:18:25.560 --> 00:18:28.637
So you are frightened you have to hold them.

00:18:28.837 --> 00:18:35.280
And there are some who are squares.

00:18:36.086 --> 00:18:41.475
And the square ones are carrying other squares on their heads, like bhoots.

00:18:41.675 --> 00:18:45.368
So if you raise them they may all topple down,

00:18:45.568 --> 00:18:49.840
or maybe the bhoots might fall off. God knows.

00:18:50.040 --> 00:18:55.520
But there are third type who are prisms, who are like pyramids,

00:18:55.720 --> 00:18:58.971
who are nicely settled down, whatever level you raise them,

00:18:59.171 --> 00:19:04.359
they are stuck there.

00:19:06.428 --> 00:19:14.560
So those who are at the periphery are a problem, definitely, for me,

00:19:14.760 --> 00:19:21.043
because in my compassion, I cannot throw them out.

00:19:22.049 --> 00:19:26.505
And we have to help them to come out,

00:19:26.705 --> 00:19:32.823
by really now, telling them, that they have to rise.

00:19:33.024 --> 00:19:38.950
How long are we to wait for them?

00:19:39.151 --> 00:19:43.774
Everyone has to see that the peripheral people

00:19:43.975 --> 00:19:51.165
are brought in properly so that they don’t go out of Sahaja Yoga.

00:19:51.851 --> 00:19:56.011
Compassion is alright,

00:19:56.211 --> 00:20:04.640
but not at the cost of keeping the level of Sahaja Yoga lower, never.

00:20:04.840 --> 00:20:12.248
We have to raise the level of people
who are well settled in Sahaja Yoga.

00:20:12.448 --> 00:20:16.550
So everybody must try to settle down

00:20:16.750 --> 00:20:23.966
and come up to minimum standards at least.

00:20:24.166 --> 00:20:29.605
Otherwise, I am sorry, many will be sieved out.

00:20:29.805 --> 00:20:32.955
That’s for the five minutes!

00:20:33.155 --> 00:20:37.461
I’ll have another, I think, one hour or so,

00:20:37.661 --> 00:20:40.880
one and a half hour later on today.

00:20:41.081 --> 00:20:45.228
Please. Thank you very much.

00:20:46.898 --> 00:20:53.688
I would say that somebody should translate it if possible.

00:20:56.828 --> 00:20:59.508
Is it possible to translate?

00:20:59.709 --> 00:21:01.714
Yogi: We could translate it afterwards, Mother.

00:21:01.915 --> 00:21:07.108
In French then to be told them Rutumbhara Pradnya and all that.

00:21:07.735 --> 00:21:10.045
Later on you can translate.

00:21:10.246 --> 00:21:18.185
I mean those who have to go for lunch now should be English then.

00:21:22.199 --> 00:21:28.995
Then he can explain it, the first part, as you please, I don’t know.

00:21:29.196 --> 00:21:33.155
Those who are staying here, should not, those who are come, should.

00:21:33.356 --> 00:21:35.888
Is wrong.

00:21:36.089 --> 00:21:44.040
The guests must be looked after, I mean, the other way round.

00:21:46.656 --> 00:21:48.815
Now we have to divide in two halves,

00:21:49.015 --> 00:21:51.242
but I would say those who understand English should go

00:21:51.443 --> 00:21:54.029
because then Gregoire can speak about this

00:21:54.229 --> 00:21:59.305
and somebody can translate also in Italian.

