00:25:50.249 --> 00:25:55.123
about general things later on.

00:25:56.289 --> 00:25:59.154
Yes, yes.

00:25:59.392 --> 00:26:03.011
Yogi: We were just talking about your comments.

00:26:03.212 --> 00:26:05.911
For example in Islam we were talking about the Mahedi

00:26:06.111 --> 00:26:10.903
who looks like a Muslim with a beard.

00:26:13.648 --> 00:26:16.594
Yes.

00:26:16.795 --> 00:26:21.413
In Islam we were talking about the Mahedi who looks like a Muslim with a beard.

00:26:21.613 --> 00:26:27.080
And in Buddhism they are talking about a Maitreya who is like a man.

00:26:27.281 --> 00:26:31.962
Every religion is talking about a coming who is in their own form,

00:26:32.162 --> 00:26:36.620
I mean, projecting. What about this?

00:26:36.820 --> 00:26:42.063
But they are all talking about your coming.

00:26:42.264 --> 00:26:48.160
Many of these scriptures are mutilated and changed also.

00:26:48.360 --> 00:26:54.890
And Buddha is, of course, is a laughing Buddha.

00:26:55.090 --> 00:26:58.065
They think of ‘laughing Buddha’.

00:26:58.265 --> 00:27:04.320
Then because it was Mohammed Sahib they think of a fakir.

00:27:04.520 --> 00:27:12.854
Because your mind is like a projector,

00:27:13.055 --> 00:27:19.612
and the film is what you have seen before, like Mohammed Sahib.

00:27:19.813 --> 00:27:27.625
So the mind projects it and you get Mohammed Sahib as the image.

00:27:28.920 --> 00:27:33.680
So whatever film you are using, it depends on [that].

00:27:33.880 --> 00:27:40.187
But whatever has happened never happens again.

00:27:41.321 --> 00:27:44.430
So if you have seen with the film, say, for example,

00:27:44.631 --> 00:27:48.720
if you have made a film, it’s made once for all.

00:27:48.920 --> 00:27:53.404
You do not make the same film, do you?

00:27:53.640 --> 00:27:57.458
I mean you are having "Mouse Trap" (play in London theatre) for so many days here,

00:27:57.658 --> 00:28:00.960
for example.

00:28:01.160 --> 00:28:05.607
But every time you see that, acting changes.

00:28:05.807 --> 00:28:12.577
And every two, three years the actors also change.

00:28:12.778 --> 00:28:15.527
So though the essence is the same going on,

00:28:15.728 --> 00:28:21.876
the same thing is now going to be repeated.
Mohammed Sahib’s life is not going to be repeated.

00:28:22.077 --> 00:28:26.025
Nor is He going to come in the way he came as a fakir.

00:28:26.225 --> 00:28:34.177
No. That has never happened in the history, why will it happen?

00:28:34.542 --> 00:28:37.360
So every time whatever has to happen has to be new.

00:28:37.560 --> 00:28:47.797
That’s the style the Nature is. It doesn’t
want to bore you say with the same (laughing).

00:28:49.360 --> 00:28:54.080
And that kind of life [is] no more needed also.

00:28:54.280 --> 00:28:58.271
And thirdly, as the seed grows,

00:28:58.471 --> 00:29:03.836
first the roots have to fight a lot to embed the seed,

00:29:04.040 --> 00:29:10.118
and then shoot has to fight a lot, but when the tree is there,

00:29:10.319 --> 00:29:16.590
then it supports others, it helps others.

00:29:16.790 --> 00:29:22.830
It becomes a strong flowering plant or a flowering tree.

00:29:23.030 --> 00:29:29.870
So the whole thing is changed every moment, which is no more the seed.

00:29:30.070 --> 00:29:35.082
But people want to see
the seed again. Why?

00:29:36.150 --> 00:29:42.190
You are identified. It’s very subtle identification.

00:29:42.390 --> 00:29:48.008
Christians are more identified with Christ than with Mohammed Sahib.

00:29:48.230 --> 00:29:50.590
Why?

00:29:50.790 --> 00:29:56.830
While the Muslims are much more identified with Mohammed Sahib.

00:29:57.030 --> 00:30:01.142
But why?

00:30:01.343 --> 00:30:03.691
Is there any reason?

00:30:03.892 --> 00:30:10.525
They equally intensely identified, for no rhyme and reason.

00:30:11.430 --> 00:30:16.110
None of Them gave them Realisation.

00:30:16.310 --> 00:30:22.270
They told the same thing. But why this identification so much with this?

00:30:22.470 --> 00:30:27.370
Now, when you are walking, you are thirsty, you see a river,

00:30:27.570 --> 00:30:32.473
whether it is the river

00:30:32.673 --> 00:30:38.990
Ganges or Jamuna or any other river, if you are thirsty,  you will drink.

00:30:39.190 --> 00:30:41.870
You won’t say, "No, I won’t drink because the Ganges is not here."

00:30:42.070 --> 00:30:48.030
Now supposing I, say, in London, "I will
only have the Ganges water." Will I have?

00:30:48.230 --> 00:30:50.910
But there are mad people I tell you, even in India.

00:30:51.110 --> 00:30:56.376
I was told some people brought the water of Ganges and the clay from there

00:30:56.577 --> 00:31:03.990
to clean their hands here, from India. I mean they can do it.

00:31:09.830 --> 00:31:12.670
This is what Sahaja Yogis must understand:

00:31:12.870 --> 00:31:17.230
that drop out your identifications with the past life.

00:31:17.430 --> 00:31:21.230
If you are born a Christian, alright, so what?

00:31:21.430 --> 00:31:28.110
Now you are a Sahaja Yogi. If you are born as a Muslim, so what?

00:31:28.310 --> 00:31:32.742
Now you are a Sahaja Yogi. The second part, what happens to you,

00:31:32.943 --> 00:31:36.074
I’ll tell you when we have the second lecture

00:31:36.274 --> 00:31:44.184
that, as a Sahaja Yogi, how things drop out, automatically.

00:31:44.384 --> 00:31:46.750
Alright?

00:31:46.950 --> 00:31:49.414
So these people

00:31:49.614 --> 00:31:53.390
are not the ones who are really following any religion whatsoever.

00:31:53.590 --> 00:31:57.550
They are following their ego religion, that’s what.

00:31:57.750 --> 00:32:00.430
There’s no religion in this kind of thing.

00:32:00.630 --> 00:32:04.955
So all these identifications just should drop out

00:32:05.156 --> 00:32:08.882
when you understand.

00:32:09.083 --> 00:32:13.538
Only there’s one way of convincing them is to show

00:32:13.739 --> 00:32:17.469
that all of them who have died,

00:32:17.670 --> 00:32:24.190
who are no more here, have said that Sahaja Yoga is going to come.

00:32:24.390 --> 00:32:30.759
That’s the only way you can convince these hard nuts.

00:32:31.430 --> 00:32:36.575
This is the problem.

00:32:46.790 --> 00:32:51.430
But surprisingly Muslims never talk of Resurrection.

00:32:51.631 --> 00:32:54.134
They are not botheredabout Resurrection. They are only worried

00:32:54.335 --> 00:32:56.749
about the doomsday, like French.

00:32:56.950 --> 00:32:59.630
French are now thinking that doomsday going to come definitely.

00:32:59.830 --> 00:33:03.614
I mean somebody asked me, "Are You sure it’s going to come or it’s postponed?"

00:33:03.814 --> 00:33:10.019
I said, "Postponed, forever" (laughing).

00:33:13.910 --> 00:33:18.154
Very seriously, I tell you. Very serious people asked me that,

00:33:18.354 --> 00:33:23.550
"What do you say if doomsday is coming or not?"

00:33:23.750 --> 00:33:31.036
And they were quite disappointed because they were banking upon it (laughing).

00:33:35.990 --> 00:33:39.439
This could be with anyone. I am just saying French,

00:33:39.639 --> 00:33:42.806
because they were French who asked me, but could be anyone.

00:33:43.007 --> 00:33:49.353
I mean don’t be identified again.

00:33:53.430 --> 00:33:57.636
Like I was telling today that they show advertisements sometimes,

00:33:57.836 --> 00:34:04.565
so horrible that they will show as if some miracle is going to happen

00:34:04.765 --> 00:34:08.286
and suddenly lot of ice will break, this will happen, that will happen

00:34:08.487 --> 00:34:12.964
and what will come out is a lager.

00:34:13.270 --> 00:34:17.699
I mean really from sublime to ridiculous. Horrible.

00:34:17.899 --> 00:34:22.990
You just can’t understand that. But I really laughed you know one day.

00:34:23.190 --> 00:34:26.067
There was a gentleman sitting, he said, "Why did you laugh?"

00:34:26.268 --> 00:34:29.150
I said, "What is this? Sublime to ridiculous!" He said, "What do you mean?

00:34:29.350 --> 00:34:36.834
I like my beer!" I said, "Sorry!" That’s it.

00:34:37.190 --> 00:34:40.670
The identification is like that, you see.

00:34:40.870 --> 00:34:47.990
Even ridiculous things start looking so fine if you identified.

00:34:53.110 --> 00:34:57.662
I hope all of you are Sahaja Yogis here.

00:34:57.910 --> 00:35:04.110
Or they are still Doubting Thomas’s sitting?

00:35:04.310 --> 00:35:09.778
They will have a bad time, I must say.

00:35:10.310 --> 00:35:15.573
It’s a very powerful session.

00:35:18.390 --> 00:35:21.175
Now don’t you worry.

00:35:21.375 --> 00:35:26.922
Don’t doubt yourself, it’s alright.

00:35:30.790 --> 00:35:35.763
What about other questions? That was a good one.

00:35:35.990 --> 00:35:40.772
Don’t depend on their images.

00:35:41.510 --> 00:35:47.836
That’s why these days most of the gurus are keeping dadees.

00:35:51.830 --> 00:35:56.750
It’s very easy to grow there. I can’t.

00:35:56.950 --> 00:36:00.013
